# Domain Architecture

## Identity Model

| Entity | Role |
|--------|------|
| **Program** | School/club identity |
| **Team** | Competition team identity; linked to Program via `Team.programId` |
| **League** | Competition context — **not** a Program |

## Player & Roster

- **`Player.currentProgramId`** — profile metadata only; not a substitute for roster history
- **`PlayerTeamSeason`** — roster assignment history (source of truth for who played where/when)

## Historical Evidence

- **`Game`** and **`GameStat`** — historical evidence
- Do **not** rewrite games or stats during normal transfers, merges, or roster moves
- Preserve historical integrity above convenience

## Rankings

| Source | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| **`PlayerRating`** | Live public rankings |
| **`RankingSnapshot`** | Historical and trend data |

## Rating Formulas

| Version | Status |
|---------|--------|
| **Formula v1** | Production |
| **Formula v2** | Experimental — not approved for production; preview/dry-run only |

## Age Groups

Official groups: **U13**, **U16**, **U19**

- U13: age 13 and below
- U16: ages 14–16
- U19: ages 17–19

Public eligibility uses **calendar age as of the evaluation date** (birthday-based). Graduation follows the class-year rule (removed from U19 starting June 1 of class year).

Carryover on age advance is **planned, not implemented** in Formula v1.

## Guiding Principle

When design choices conflict, **preserve historical integrity** over convenience shortcuts.
